# Laragon PHP 8.2 (shore-reporting)

This repo targets **PHP 8.2+**. On Windows, the system `php` may be older (e.g. 8.0). **Always use Laragon’s PHP 8.2** for Artisan and Composer in shell commands.

## Executable (canonical)

```text
C:\laragon\bin\php\php-8.2.0-Win32-vs16-x64\php.exe
```

If Laragon’s folder name under `C:\laragon\bin\php\` changes (e.g. you upgrade 8.2), update this path in **`.vscode/settings.json`** and in this rule.

## Running Artisan

Do **not** run plain `php artisan …` unless the terminal’s `PATH` already puts Laragon PHP 8.2 first (workspace terminal usually does via `.vscode/settings.json`).

**Preferred when invoking from the agent (explicit):**

```powershell
& "C:\laragon\bin\php\php-8.2.0-Win32-vs16-x64\php.exe" artisan migrate
& "C:\laragon\bin\php\php-8.2.0-Win32-vs16-x64\php.exe" artisan serve
```

Same pattern for **Composer** if needed:

```powershell
& "C:\laragon\bin\php\php-8.2.0-Win32-vs16-x64\php.exe" C:\laragon\bin\composer\composer.phar install
```

## Workspace terminal

`terminal.integrated.env.windows` in **`.vscode/settings.json`** prepends Laragon PHP 8.2 to `PATH` for integrated terminals so `php artisan` works there after reload.
